==English==
===Noun===
'''filetype''' (''plural'': '''[[filetypes]]''')
#An identifier for the type of information contained in an electronic format.
#A command in certain [[operating system]]s that creates a directory of files of a particular type or sorted by type, or that limits the results of a directory search to a particular type.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|filetyp|e}}
#To sort files by the type of information contained therein.
#:''This software searches the directory and attempts to '''filetype''' all the files in it.''